[{"id":"VR004884","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Bismuth-214 <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis bismuth-214 with atomic number 83 close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis bismuth-214 with atomic number 83 close parenthesis\"><mrow><mo>(</mo><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mmultiscripts><mrow><mtext>Bi</mtext></mrow><mprescripts><mrow><mn>83</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>214</mn></mrow></mprescripts></mmultiscripts><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></mrow></math></span></span> is unstable with a half-life of 5 days and decays into polonium-214 <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis polonium-214 with atomic number 84 close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis polonium-214 with atomic number 84 close parenthesis\"><mrow><mo>(</mo><mmultiscripts><mrow><mtext>Po</mtext></mrow><mprescripts><mrow><mn>84</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>214</mn></mrow></mprescripts></mmultiscripts><mo>)</mo></mrow></math></span></span>, which has a half-life of 138 days. An initial number <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N sub 0\"><math alttext=\"N sub 0\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>N</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></math></span></span> of Bismuth-214 nuclei are placed in a container and its contents are checked after 10 days. Which of the following correctly predicts the ratio of bismuth-214 nuclei to polonium-214 nuclei in the container and the correct type of emission?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR004884_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">3:4; beta particle emission</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">3:1; alpha particle emission</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">4:3; alpha particle emission</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">1:3; beta particle emission</p>"],"answer":3}]